events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — The Cavaliers made sure things didn't go from bad to worse.
headlines.shortLinkText: Goodwin's 21 help Cavs beat Pelicans 93-90 without Garland

headlines.description: — Indiana Pacers rookie Isaiah Jackson celebrated his best game of the season with an unexpected bath.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson's breakout game sends Pacers past Clippers 122-116

headlines.description: — Tyrese Maxey scored 33 points, including a driving layup with 26.4 seconds left in overtime that put Philadelphia ahead for good, and the 76ers beat the Memphis Grizzlies 122-119 without Joel Embiid on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maxey leads 76ers past Grizzlies 122-119 in OT minus Embiid

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown had 29 points, Jayson Tatum added 20 points and 12 rebounds and the Boston Celtics rolled past the Miami Heat 122-92 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown scores 29, Celtics run past shorthanded Heat 122-92

events.name: Sacramento Kings at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Alec Burks had 21 points off the bench, Evan Fournier also scored 21 and the New York Knicks routed the skidding Sacramento Kings 116-96 on Monday night to snap a three-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Burks, Fournier lead Knicks to 116-96 win over Kings

headlines.description: — Gary Trent Jr. scored 31 points, Pascal Siakam added 23 and the Toronto Raptors snapped Atlanta’s seven-game winning streak with a 106-100 victory on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors end Hawks' 7-game win streak behind Trent, Siakam

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry capped a subpar January with an offensive masterpiece Monday night against the Houston Rockets that served as a reminder of just how dangerous he can be.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry heats up late to lead Warriors over Rockets 122-108

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — In their first game since leading scorer Shai Gilgeous-Alexander was injured, the Oklahoma City Thunder scrapped their way to a win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dort helps Thunder top Trail Blazers 98-81, end 7-game skid
